Name: typeutil
Synopsis: Helpers for type inflection and simplifying working with Golang generic interface types

Functions.Name: Auto
Functions.Comment: Package-level auto converter

Functions.Name: Bool
Functions.Comment: Package-level bool converter

Functions.Name: Bytes
Functions.Comment: Package-level bytes converter

Functions.Name: Dump
Functions.Comment: Returns a pretty-printed string representation of the given values.

Functions.Name: Dumpf
Functions.Comment: Returns a pretty-printed string representation of the given values.

Functions.Name: Duration
Functions.Comment: Package-level duration converter

Functions.Name: Err
Functions.Comment: Package-level error converter

Functions.Name: Float
Functions.Comment: Package-level float converter

Functions.Name: FunctionArity
Functions.Comment: Returns the number of input and return arguments a given function has.

Functions.Name: Int
Functions.Comment: Package-level int64 converter

Functions.Name: IsArray
Functions.Comment: Returns whether the given value is a slice or array.

Functions.Name: IsEmpty
Functions.Comment:
Returns whether the given value is "empty" in the semantic sense. Zero values
are considered empty, as are arrays, slices, and maps containing only empty
values (called recursively). Finally, strings are trimmed of whitespace and
considered empty if the result is zero-length.

Functions.Name: IsFloat
Functions.Comment: Returns whether the given value represents a floating point value.

Functions.Name: IsFunction
Functions.Comment: Returns whether the given value is a function of any kind

Functions.Name: IsFunctionArity
Functions.Comment:
Returns whether the given value is a function.  If inParams is not -1, the function must
accept that number of arguments.  If outParams is not -1, the function must return that
number of values.
Functions.Signature: IsFunctionArity(in interface{}, inParams int, outParams int) bool

Functions.Name: IsInteger
Functions.Comment: Returns whether the given value represents an integer value.

Functions.Name: IsKind
Functions.Comment:
Dectect whether the concrete underlying value of the given input is one or more
Kinds of value.

Functions.Name: IsMap
Functions.Comment: Returns whether the given value is a map.

Functions.Name: IsNumeric
Functions.Comment: Returns whether the given value represents a numeric value.

Functions.Name: IsScalar
Functions.Comment:
Return whether the given input is a discrete scalar value (ints, floats, bools,
strings), otherwise known as "primitive types" in some other languages.

Functions.Name: IsStruct
Functions.Comment: Returns whether the given value is a struct.

Functions.Name: IsZero
Functions.Comment: Returns whether the given value represents the underlying type's zero value

Functions.Name: Len
Functions.Comment:
Returns the length of the given value that could have a length (strings, slices, arrays,
maps, and channels).  If the value is not a type that has a length, -1 is returned.

Functions.Name: Map
Functions.Comment: Package-level map converter

Functions.Name: MapNative
Functions.Comment: Package-level map[string]interface{} converter

Functions.Name: NInt
Functions.Comment: Package-level native int converter

Functions.Name: RegisterTypeHandler
Functions.Comment:
Register's a handler used for converting one type to another. Type are checked in the following
manner:  The input value's reflect.Type String() value is matched, falling back to its
reflect.Kind String() value, finally checking for a special "*" value that matches any type.
If the handler function returns nil, its value replaces the input value.  If the special error
type PassthroughType is returned, the original value is returned unmodified.

Functions.Name: ResolveValue
Functions.Comment:
Return the concrete value pointed to by a pointer type, or within an
interface type.  Allows functions receiving pointers to supported types
to work with those types without doing reflection.

Functions.Name: SetValue
Functions.Comment: Attempts to set the given reflect.Value to the given interface value

Functions.Comment: Package-level slice converter

Functions.Comment: Package-level string splitter.

Functions.Name: String
Functions.Comment: Package-level string converter

Functions.Name: Strings
Functions.Comment: Package-level string slice converter

Functions.Name: Time
Functions.Comment: Package-level time converter

Variant.Name: Variant

Methods.Name: Auto
Methods.Comment: Return the value automatically converted to the appropriate type.

Methods.Name: Bool
Methods.Comment: Return true if the value can be interpreted as a boolean true value, or false otherwise.

Methods.Name: Bytes
Methods.Comment: Return the value at key as a byte slice.

Methods.Name: Duration
Methods.Comment: Return the value as a time.Duration if it can be interpreted as such, or zero otherwise.

Methods.Name: Err
Methods.Comment: Return the value converted to an error, or nil if it is not an error.

Methods.Name: Float
Methods.Comment: Return the value as a float if it can be interpreted as such, or 0 otherwise.

Methods.Name: Int
Methods.Comment:
Return the value as an integer if it can be interpreted as such, or 0 otherwise. Float values
will be truncated to integers.

Methods.Name: IsArray
Methods.Comment: Return whether the value is an array/slice type.

Methods.Name: IsMap
Methods.Comment: Return whether the value is a map type.

Methods.Name: IsNil
Methods.Comment: Returns whether the underlying value is nil.

Methods.Name: IsScalar
Methods.Comment: Return whether the value is a scalar type.

Methods.Name: IsZero
Methods.Comment: Returns whether the underlying value is a zero value.

Methods.Name: Map
Methods.Comment:
Return the value as a map[Variant]Variant if it can be interpreted as such, or an empty map otherwise.
If the variant contains a struct, and a tagName is specified, the key names of the output map will be taken
from the struct field's tag value, consistent with the rules used in encoding/json.

Methods.Name: MapNative
Methods.Comment: Return the value as a map[string]interface{} if it can be interpreted as such, or an empty map otherwise.

Methods.Name: MarshalJSON
Methods.Comment: Satisfy the json.Marshaler interface

Methods.Name: NInt
Methods.Comment:
Return the value as a native integer if it can be interpreted as such, or 0 otherwise.
Float values will be truncated to integers.

Methods.Name: Slice
Methods.Comment:
Return the value as a slice of Variants. Scalar types will return a slice containing
a single Variant element representing the value.

Methods.Name: Split
Methods.Comment: Converts the value to a string, then splits on the given delimiter.

Methods.Name: String
Methods.Comment: Return the value as a string, or an empty string if the value could not be converted.

Methods.Name: Strings
Methods.Comment: Same as Slice(), but returns a []string.

Methods.Name: Time
Methods.Comment: Return the value as a time.Time if it can be interpreted as such, or zero time otherwise.

Methods.Name: V
Methods.Comment: Shortcut for creating a Variant.

Variant.Comment:
Represents an interface type with helper functions for making it easy to do
type conversions.
